Section 5 - Duties of the Vice President 

	The Vice President shall assume the duties of the President in the event that
  the President is absent or for any reason temporarily unable to fulfill those
  duties. 

	In the event that the position of President becomes vacant, the Vice President
  shall assume the position of President until the next General Meeting. 

	A copy of all relevant correspondence received or sent by the Vice President 
  on behalf of the GCCC shall be passed to the Secretary. 

	The Vice President shall assist the President as required. 

	The Vice-President shall coordinate with the Secretary and Treasurer to
  produce the necessary financial records for the GCCC. 

